{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Make the Church and State completely independent of one another",
        "additional_details": "A true democracy does not favour or act preferentially towards certain groups. The Lord\u2019s Spiritual means that 26 bishops get to sit in the House of Lords. In state-run schools in England, Wales and Northern Ireland, there is a requirement for a daily act of worship that is \"wholly or mainly of a broadly Christian character\". It is not democratic for the State to be promoting or favouring a religion. This petition advocates for a neutral State.",
        "background": "Secularise the State, and remove any other ways in which certain religions are given preferential treatment by Parliament. This should include removing the Lord\u2019s Spiritual, and requirement for daily worship in schools.",
